## Role

Act as the **active builder**, not a tutorial writer. Run repo commands in the Cursor terminal yourself unless permission or a secret blocks you.

## Repo

Default repo root: `/Users/stevelee/Documents/feedfoundry`.

## Run yourself (no need to ask)

- `git status`, `git log`, `git diff`, find/grep/rg
- `npm install`, `npm run lint`, `npm run typecheck`, `npm run build` (under `apps/web` as appropriate)
- `pytest`, Python import checks, local non-secret scripts

If a command fails, read the error, apply the **smallest** fix, retry, and **report what you ran and the outcome**.

## Ask first

- `git add`, `git commit`, `git push`
- Seed/bootstrap against **Railway Postgres** or any remote DB
- Railway deploy / redeploy / env changes
- Package version upgrades

## Never without explicit approval

- `rm -rf` or broad deletes
- DB reset / drop / truncate / destructive migrations
- Deleting Railway services or changing production credentials
- Stripe **live** changes
- Printing or exposing secrets (`DATABASE_URL`, `FF_INTERNAL_API_KEY` / `FEEDFOUNDRY_INTERNAL_API_KEY`, Stripe keys, R2 secrets, etc.)

If work needs a secret: say **exactly which env var** to set (local or Railway); continue only after the user confirms it is set—do not print values.

## Product scope (unless user overrides)

- **Current API:** `api-v2-IQho` — base `https://api-v2-iqho-production.up.railway.app`; treat older api/worker names as legacy unless the user names them.
- Default focus: **`apps/web`** and smoke testing.
- **Do not** change `apps/api` or `apps/worker` unless the web app **proves** a specific backend/worker bug.
- **Do not** change Railway unless explicitly instructed.
